'''ClearCheckbook.com''' is a [[freemium]], [[web-based]] personal money management tool created by Brandon O'Brien.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clearcheckbook.com/about|title=The ClearCheckbook Story}}</ref>

==About==
ClearCheckbook was originally conceived as a way to reconcile bank account transactions with "actual" spending (a process called ''jiving''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mdmproofing.com/iym/interviews/clear-checkbook-brandon-obrien.html|title=Interview with Brandon O'Brien, Creator, ClearCheckbook.com|date=Feb 20, 2007}}</ref> in ClearCheckbook lingo). Since its launch in May 2006, the application has undergone three major revisions and now allows users to track bills, setup reminders and recurring transactions, create spending reports, set budgets and more.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clearcheckbook.com/tour|title=ClearCheckbook Tour}}</ref> According to the reports, It is said that ClearCheckbook manages two million transactions for over 17,800 active users.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2326030,00.asp|title=15 Web Sites for Managing (and Saving) Money|work=PCMAG|access-date=2017-11-14|language=en}}</ref>

