== Functionality == Service Manager is an [[IT service management#Tools for ITSM|ITSM Tool]] using the [[ITIL]] framework providing a web interface for corporate changes, releases and interactions ([[ITIL#Request fulfillment|request fulfillment]]) supported by a [[Service catalog]] and [[CMDB]]. For a summary of the functionality, screenshots, data sheets, white papers and more information refer to the sources listed above.
== Propel == [http://www8.hp.com/au/en/software-solutions/propel-service-broker-catalog/index.html Propel] is a separate web frontend providing a cut down view of HP Service Manager functions. This front end can be tailored to business requirements for service request, incident and change ticket management.
